criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        • patients with liver failure undergoing liver transplantation

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Age less than 18 years;

          -  Active overt infection;

          -  Patients on oral or systemic anticoagulation or with known coagulopathic disorders
             apart from those caused by liver failure (eg.: Protein C or S deficiency, congenital
             platelet disorders and congenital coagulation disorders…etc);

          -  Patients undergoing re-transplantation.
